'''''morchant''''' is a [[Sindarin]] word meaning ''shadow'', as in the shadow of an object cast by light.  It also means ''dark shape''.  It probably derives from ''[[morn]]'' "dark" and ''[[cant]]'' "shape".

==Synonyms==
* ''[[gwath]]''
* ''[[dae]]''
* ''[[dúath]]''
